            <thetext>Find a way to automatically (as much as possible) set the svn:ignore property. 
This would be helpful e.g. when adding a new bug under qooxdoo-contrib/Bugs so 
they would instantly ignore &#39;cache&#39; directories.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>8433</commentid>
            <who name="Derrell Lipman">derrell.lipman</who>
            <bug_when>2009-03-09 15:13:52 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>I&#39;m not sure it&#39;s ubiquitous (it may only work with the standard Linux svn client), but maybe it works globally. You can create a file in the root of the svn tree called &quot;.svnignore&quot; and in it put one line per entry to ignore. You&#39;ll want to check in this file so each user&#39;s checkout gets it. It&#39;s used on the client side. For example, your top-level .svnignore file might look like this:

*~
cache
build
</thetext>
          </long_desc>
